The paper discusses the properties of wide minima in deep neural networks, which is a topic related to machine learning and optimization. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the convergence of ResNets, which is a type of neural network architecture, indicating that it may also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper discusses the characteristics of both linear and nonlinear models, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper discusses the signal path from input to output, which is related to signal processing, indicating that it may also belong to cs.SI (Signal and Image Processing).
